⚙️ Technical
Topic: Operating System (OS)
1️⃣ Clear Theory (Easy Language)

An Operating System (OS) is software that:

Acts as a bridge between user and hardware

Manages resources (CPU, memory, files)

📌 Examples:

Windows

Linux

macOS

Android

2️⃣ Important Concepts
🔹 Process

A program in execution

Example: Running Chrome, VS Code

🔹 CPU Scheduling

OS decides which process runs first

Types:

FCFS (First Come First Serve)

SJF (Shortest Job First)

Round Robin

🔹 Memory Management

OS manages RAM efficiently

🔹 Deadlock

When processes wait forever
👉 Example: Two people waiting for each other

🔹 Threads

Small units of a process

Help in multitasking

3️⃣ Functions of OS

Process management

Memory management

File system management

Device management

🧠 Quick Tricks

OS = Manager of system

Process = Running program

Deadlock = Waiting forever

Thread = Small task

